he light from the laser; a detector (<b>26</b>) that detects output power of the laser and generates a laser power detection signal; a laser power control circuit (<b>27</b>) that controls the output power of the laser using the laser power detection signal; a detector (<b>10</b>) that detects a gap length between the optical disk and the SIL and generates a gap detection signal; and a gap control circuit (<b>15</b>) that controls the gap length between the optical disk and the SIL using the gap detection signal. The power control circuit has a gain crossover frequency greater than a gain crossover frequency of the gap control circuit.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>